  "texts": [
    "We estimated PBS for the coding region of each gene, as well as 5 kb on both the 5′ (hereafter upstream) and the 3′ ends (hereafter downstream).",
    "Thus, each gene has three PBS values.",
    "Genic and non-genic regions in the top 1% of their respective PBS distributions were considered selection candidates.",
    "Across the four populations, this candidate cutoff resulted in 1016 5 kb upstream candidates, 915 coding region candidates, and 1003 in the 5 kb downstream region (Fig. 5B).The vast majority of PBS candidate genes are unique to each population.",
    "This pattern is similar to that observed among the differentially expressed genes, which again suggests defense responses are often population specific."
  ],
